-- Health Secretary Lansley Says U.K. Considering Plain Cigarette Packaging
-- B y   R o b e r t   H u t t o n
-- 2010-11-28T09:33:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-28/health-secretary-lansley-says-u-k-considering-plain-cigarette-packaging.html
U.K. Health Secretary Andrew Lansley
says tobacco is “a serious public health issue” and the
government is considering forcing tobacco companies to package
cigarettes in plain wrapping, he told the BBC’s Marr program
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
